    "b-interaction-intro-2": {
      "id": "b-interaction-intro-2",
      "flavour": "paragraph",
      "props": {},
      "text": [
        {
          "insert": "interaction/ is the pure-TS floor under every gesture: it defines what a pointer event IS, what a hit IS, and the shared thresholds that decide when a press becomes a drag — and it implements the DOM-free utilities (hit-testing, frame coalescing, edge-pan velocity, the clipboard) that everything above consumes. What it deliberately does NOT contain is the machine: the gesture-state union and the dispatcher assemble in "
        },
        {
          "insert": "core.ts",
          "attributes": {
            "code": true,
            "reference": {
              "kind": "source",
              "path": "packages/canvas/src/stage/editor/pipeline/core.ts",
              "label": "core.ts",
              "symbol": "stepInteraction"
            }
          }
        },
        {
          "insert": " (see "
        },
        {
          "insert": "20-implementation/50-editor",
          "attributes": {
            "reference": {
              "kind": "doc",
              "path": "20-implementation/50-editor",
              "label": "20-implementation/50-editor"
            }
          }
        },
        {
          "insert": "), each editor feature slice owns its own gesture logic, and connector gestures live in the connector slice (see "
        },
        {
          "insert": "20-implementation/30-connectors",
          "attributes": {
            "reference": {
              "kind": "doc",
              "path": "20-implementation/30-connectors",
              "label": "20-implementation/30-connectors"
            }
          }
        },
        {
          "insert": "). The barrel "
        },
        {
          "insert": "interaction.ts",
          "attributes": {
            "code": true,
            "reference": {
              "kind": "source",
              "path": "packages/canvas/src/interaction/interaction.ts",
              "label": "interaction.ts"
            }
          }
        },
        {
          "insert": " says exactly this in its header — it re-exports kernel vocabulary and nothing else."
        }
      ],
      "children": []
    },
